51.3	Chandra_X-ray_Observatory	Chandra X-ray Observatory	The Chandra X-ray Observatory is a satellite launched on STS-93 by NASA on July 23, 1999. It was named in honor of Indian physicist Subrahmanyan Chandrasekhar who is known for determining the maximum mass for white dwarfs. "Chandra" also means "moon" or "luminous" in Sanskrit.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Chandra_X-ray_Observatory_inside_the_Space_Shuttle_payload_bay.jpg/250px-Chandra_X-ray_Observatory_inside_the_Space_Shuttle_payload_bay.jpg
